    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>There were two robbers Kali and Vikrant who came across a hidden cave. When they went inside ,they saw a stack of gold plates kept there. Each plate has a money value written on it which he will get when he sells them. They decided to play a game .<br />\nIn each turn the player can take 1,2 or 3 gold plates from the top. Both the players play optimally but Kali starts first. Now you have to tell what is the maximum money Kali will get when he sells his gold plates.</p>\n<p><b>See Sample I/O for clarifications</b>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>First line is <b>T</b> , the number of testcases Then <b>2T</b> lines follow , 2 lines for each testcase.<br /><br />\nThe first line contains <b>N</b> , the number of gold plates in the stack<br /><br />\nSecond line consists of <b>N</b> integers denoting the money value of plates </p>\n<p><b>Note:</b> The first element denotes top of the stack and the last element the bottom of thestack.</p>\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>For each test case, output the answer which is the maximum money value Kali can get on selling his plates.</p>\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>5</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>100000</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>Money Value on a plate</b> \u2264 <b>1000000000</b></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n2\n3\n1 2 3\n4\n1 1 3 4\n<b>Output:</b>\n6\n5\n</pre><p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Case 2.</b><br />\nKali takes the plates with values 1,1,3 and Vikrant takes the plate with value 4 . So Kali can get maximum money value = 1+1+3 =5.</p>\n",
